\- a record is a set of named values wrapped in { }.
   keys use the same - delimiter as parameters. -\

\- multi-line: opening brace on the definition line, body indented,
   never a brace stranded alone -\

#keeper: {
  name - Aldous Vane
  years at post - 31
  lamp lit - true
}

\- short records fit on one line, comma-separated -\

#world: { location - Bag End, time - night, storm - true }

\- records nest -\

#keeper_detailed: {
  name - Aldous Vane
  posted - Dunmore Head
  history { years - 31, incidents - 2 }
}

\- record values can be any literal: strings, numbers, booleans -\

#report: {
  title - Q3 Operations Review
  author - Mara Finch
  quarter - Q3 2024
  status - final
}
